+        "decomposition C = (kappa_c, kappa_s, kappa_int) MOVES within the "
+        "fiber but its sum is fixed: delta C in ker Sigma (Sigma: Q^3 -> Q, "
+        "Sigma(a,b,c)=a+b+c), i.e. delta K_G = 0. The single-edge law (a "
+        "symbolic identity over Q in (t, g, H)) is delta kappa_c(t e_i) = "
+        "4 t (prod g) H_jk / q^2, where {j,k} is the index pair complementary "
+        "to i (equivalently delta Delta_c = -4 t (prod g) H_jk; Delta_c uses "
+        "q^2). At the keystone F8 (g=(3,1,2), H=[[2,1,0],[1,0,0],[0,0,2]], "
